snippet.textDisplay:
I would say I'm sorry to see Shadow in the situation it is but I've tried their service.... It was awful not only did I get horrible performance in games I also had horrible lag and stutter if I ran anything in fullscreen so I had to run shadow in windowed mode with a windowed game. I only got around 50fps on GTA online 1080p very high versus my 1660 super which gives me 70-80fps.... Which the Shadow GPU is supposed to be a 1080 ti equivalent but I call BS unless I was being forced to share a GPU which they claim doesn't happen. Regardless though even overlooking the performance issues the bugs were problem enough to just not even consider it. That's why I bought the prebuilt on sale instead of sticking with shadow and I am glad I did not sign up for a year that's for sure because I was considering it.

Don't get me wrong I'm sure it will get better with time but currently it just feels like a beta product and I feel like a beta tester that's paying for the service... I'm just not for it not for the performance it gives plus now I have a prebuilt and even though the Shadow PC allegedly has better specs my PC outperforms it by far.
